<item>
            <title>[LU-5734] LNet dynamic control: lnet_dyn_add_ni() can&apos;t clean up failed NI in some cases</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5734</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In lnet_dyn_add_ni(), if lnet_startup_lndnis() fails, then NI on the local &amp;amp;net_head list is freed. But lnet_startup_lndnis(&amp;amp;net_head) can fail after list_del(&amp;amp;ni-&amp;gt;ni_list), i.e. after the NI has been removed already from the &amp;amp;net_head. In this case I failed to see where the NI gets cleaned up and freed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
